Version 1.2.4
centos 7

# Create graph using script as data input
1 create script with output format "string:value" note the ":"
text:number  ---> remember the format
download:23232 upload:24335


The script should be saved in /usr/share/cacti/scripts file permission should be like
-rwxr-xr-x 1 apache apache   test.py
the permission for others can be removed

2 create data input methods
  2.1 add output fields - it must match the outout field name of script eg. if output is --- download:2341 upload:34321

then data output field will be "download" and "upload" outof context example

3 add data template
  3.1 add data source item
    the data source items should be match the output filed names

4 create graph template
   4.1 add graph template items

5 add device to graph from ...

   Graphs will be populated after 10 or 15 minutes as you configured

     
